E. COLI 0157 - JAPAN (4)
========================
[see also archive.960614, archive.960617]
CHUGOKU shinbun newspaper report on May [June?] 18--
_E. coli_ O157 mass food poisoning is spreading in Japan. New cases were
reported from FUKUOKA and NAGOYA Prefectures. Five prefectures (OKAYAMA,
HIROSHIMA, AICHI, GIFU, and FUKUOKA) reported O157 _E. coli_.
Health Ministry started DNA analysis from them [isolates]. A comparison of
DNA patterns will provide information whether contaminated foods are the same
or not.
From NIIMI-cho, OKAYAMA
-----------------------
OKAYAMA Prefecture announced that a total of 300 students of seven
elementary school and one junior high school complained of food poisoning
symptoms, such as stomach ache and/or diarrhea; 21 students were hospitalized.
O157 was detected from a sixth grade elementary school girl. The cause of
the mass food poisoning was not confirmed to O157.
At SHISEI elementary school, 101 students, one-sixth of the total students,
were absent and [the school was] temporarily closed on JUNE 21.
The lunch supply center was already temporarily closed, and the closing was
prolonged to JUNE 21.
From Tojyo town, HIROSHIMA
--------------------------
On [June] 17th, O157 was detected from four students and one teacher; 18
additional students complained of symptoms.
Total O157 detected: 35 students, 6 teachers, 1 family.
Total case (incl.suspected): 185 students.
[The following was received from Dr. Kikuchi separately but is included for
the sake of completeness and continuity.]
This is from a nationwide newspaper ASAHI SHINBUN.
June 19:
OKAYAMA
-------
A total of 468 cases were reported from students, teachers, and families of
four elementary schools and three kindergartens in Oku town, OKAYAMA; eight
people have been hospitalized.
A total of 290 cases were reported from the students of seven elementary
school and one junior high school in Niimi town. On [June] 18, 24 (total 45)
were hospitalized. Their lunch supply center was temporarily closed for 7
days, from June 18.
Sporadic cases were reported from Okayama City. O157 was detected from two
adults and one child (3 years old). They live in different areas from each
other. No [epidemiologic] relation has been found between these cases.
HIROSHIMA
---------
In total, O157 was detected from 36 students, six teachers, and one family
of Tojyo elementary school. The school was temporarily closed for 3 days,
from June 19.
On June 18, O157 was detected in one new case. She is 10 years old and
complained of sickness from June 7. A total of 186 cases have been reported.
GIFU
----
Mass food poisoning was reported from Nagamori-Minami elementary school,
GIFU. A total of 347 students and teachers complain of sickness. The
bacteria was detected in 66 students. ([Identification as to whether this
was] O157 was not mentioned in the article.)
AICHI
-----
20 students complain of sickness from Takamoridai Junior High School,
Kasugai City. All of them were in the second grade of the school and joined
the school camp at Ena district. They [purportedly] were infected at the
camp.
FUKUOKA
-------
O157 was detected from seven pupils of a kindergarten.
--
H. Kikuchi, M.D.
Hiroshima Quarantine Officer
Hiroshima Quarantine Station, Japan
<MHH00326@niftyserve.or.jp>
